#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_reflectionprobe.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_reflectionprobe.rst:19
msgid ""
"Captures its surroundings as a cubemap, and stores versions of it with "
"increasing levels of blur to simulate different material roughnesses."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_reflectionprobe.rst:21
msgid ""
"The ``ReflectionProbe`` is used to create high-quality reflections at the"
" cost of performance. It can be combined with :ref:`GIProbe "
"<class_GIProbe>`\\ s and Screen Space Reflections to achieve high quality"
" reflections. ``ReflectionProbe``\\ s render all objects within their "
":ref:`cull_mask <class_ReflectionProbe_property_cull_mask>`, so updating "
"them can be quite expensive. It is best to update them once with the "
"important static objects and then leave them."
msgstr ""

