#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_reflectionprobe.rst:68
msgid ""
"**UPDATE_ONCE** = **0** --- Update the probe once on the next frame. The "
"corresponding radiance map will be generated over the following six "
"frames. This is slower to update than :ref:`UPDATE_ALWAYS "
"<class_ReflectionProbe_constant_UPDATE_ALWAYS>` but can result in higher "
"quality reflections."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_reflectionprobe.rst:70
msgid ""
"**UPDATE_ALWAYS** = **1** --- Update the probe every frame. This is "
"needed when you want to capture dynamic objects. However, it results in "
"an increased render time. Use :ref:`UPDATE_ONCE "
"<class_ReflectionProbe_constant_UPDATE_ONCE>` whenever possible."
msgstr ""

